    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSetting the `background` option to \"light\" during the startup process using lua (`vim.opt` or `vim.o`) does not work.\r\n\r\nHowever using vimscript for the same configuration works fine: `set background=light`.\r\n\r\nOther options I tested (for example `number`) work fine,  but I haven't tested them all, so there might be more affected.\r\n\r\nAfter startup setting the `background` option using lua works just fine.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim --clean --cmd 'lua vim.opt.background=\"light\"'`\r\nOR\r\n`nvim --clean --cmd 'lua vim.o.background=\"light\"'`\r\n\r\nAfterwards check the `background` option via `:set background`\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe `background` option should be set to \"light\"\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1031+gc431d820e\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 20.04.6 LTS\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGNOME Terminal 3.36.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
    "closed_at": "2023-09-05T12:03:27Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "This should fix it:\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/option.c b/src/nvim/option.c\r\nindex cc3a9c181..ae4e7c1fd 100644\r\n--- a/src/nvim/option.c\r\n+++ b/src/nvim/option.c\r\n@@ -3772,7 +3772,7 @@ static const char *set_option(int opt_idx, void *varp, OptVal *v, int opt_flags,\r\n                                errbuf, errbuflen);\r\n   }\r\n \r\n-  if (errmsg != NULL) {\r\n+  if (errmsg == NULL) {\r\n     did_set_option(opt_idx, opt_flags, true, value_checked);\r\n   }\r\n \r\n```",
